  "designDecisions": [
    "Single in-memory store singleton (src/lib/store.ts) with exported mutable Maps for Users, Projects, Boards, Columns, Tasks, Comments — persists for the lifetime of the Node.js process, survives hot-reload via module caching",
    "Seed data (src/lib/seed.ts) pre-populates one demo team, two users (admin@demo.com / member@demo.com, password: 'password'), one project, one board, three columns, and six sample tasks so the app is immediately usable without registration",
    "Auth uses a lightweight session: POST /api/auth/login sets an HttpOnly cookie 'session' containing a JSON-encoded { userId, expires } payload signed with a static HMAC secret baked into src/lib/auth.ts — no external JWT library needed",
    "Middleware (src/middleware.ts) protects all /dashboard, /board, /projects, /analytics routes by checking the session cookie and redirecting to /login if absent or expired",
    "Drag-and-drop implemented using the native HTML5 Drag and Drop API with React synthetic events (onDragStart, onDragOver, onDrop) to avoid installing @dnd-kit or react-beautiful-dnd — works on desktop, mobile fallback via click-to-move",
    "Column ordering stored as an array of column IDs on the KanbanBoard record; task ordering stored as a 'position' integer on each Task record — both updated atomically in the move API",
    "All data fetching uses SWR-style custom hooks (useBoard, useTasks, useProjects) backed by fetch() calls to API routes with optimistic local state updates for instant UI feedback on drag-and-drop",
    "Priority is a union type ('low' | 'medium' | 'high') rendered as a colored Badge component; overdue detection is purely client-side by comparing task.dueDate to new Date()",
    "Analytics computed on-the-fly in /api/analytics from in-memory task data — no pre-aggregation table needed for MVP; charts rendered with inline SVG path calculations inside TasksChart and WorkloadChart components without Chart.js",
    "Team invitation is simulated: POST /api/team/invite immediately creates a new User record with a generated ID and adds them to the team — no actual email sending, satisfying the zero-external-services constraint",
    "Modal and Toast components are self-contained with React portals via createPortal to document.body, avoiding z-index stacking issues",
    "Tailwind config extends default theme with a custom 'kanban' color palette and a 'drag-ghost' opacity utility; no shadcn/ui or Radix dependencies",
    "All form validation is client-side using controlled inputs with inline error state — no react-hook-form or Zod to minimize dependencies",
    "The cn() utility in src/lib/utils.ts combines clsx-style conditional classes without the clsx package: a simple template-literal helper",
    "package.json pins only next, react, react-dom, typescript, tailwindcss, postcss, autoprefixer, @types/react, @types/node — all built-ins, zero third-party runtime deps beyond Next.js itself"
